// Represents a NAT gateway for outbound traffic (SNAT) from a VirtualNetwork.
//
// A NATGateway provides a dedicated egress identity for all resources within a VirtualNetwork.
// All outbound traffic from the VirtualNetwork's CIDR is source-NATted to the associated
// ExternalIP address. This gives tenants a known, stable source IP for egress traffic —
// useful for allowlisting, auditing, and compliance.
//
